etymologies: early 20th century: from proto-‘original, earlier’ + actinium, so named because one of its isotopes decays to form actinium

definitions: the chemical element of atomic number 91, a radioactive metal of the actinide series, occurring in small amounts as a product of the natural decay of uranium.
shortDefinitions: chemical element of atomic number 91, radioactive metal of actinide series, occurring in small amounts as product of natural decay of uranium
